mean_en: a person who is in charge of something, especially an officer in charge of a particular group of soldiers or a military operation; an officer of fairly high rank in the British or American navy; (in Britain) a London police officer of high rank
sentence: The commander was thinking about possible strategies.
sentence_trans: 指挥官在思考下一步可行的策略。
word_etyma: com共同 + mand命令 + er表示做某事的人 → n.司令官，指挥员
